Originally Answered: What are some things you have done for your significant other to reassure him or her when they felt insecure?

One girl I dated years needed help because she felt insecure bout performing in front of people. She felt she wasn't good enough at singing because people around her were telling her so.

I asked her to sing.

I said she can sing and I set things in motion.

I called some recording studios, producers and...booked one week of recording studio time in one of the finest recording studios in town.

They owed me a favour and I called it in.

She thought I was joking but when she stepped into recording studio she knew I was god damns serious.

She got help with singing lesson. She can sing, so there was no problem and the singing lessons helped her with dynamics, techniques of singing to help her more. Then she got help for writing songs.

I got her to tell me somethings about her life and wrote the lyrics for her, sorted some chords out, for structure of whole song and the producer started putting it all together with the beats, etc.

One week later, she had a song and....the big surprise.

There was an event in the city. I knew then organiser. So I asked if he can slot her in and that's what he did.

She performed in front of 3,000 people outside, in devonshire green, Like a music festival kind of thing, big, and she was one of the artists.

That's all she needed to boost her self esteem and belief in herself.

It sparked something in me to carry on, helping others. I was good at networking, fearless at it and had many resources, contact and I invested my own monies.

I enjoyed giving and helping not just women I date but I discovered on my journey people needed help to experience the real deal to boost their self confidence. So, it is what I have done in my free time....since I was 16 years old. I'm 45 now..
